The paper deals with generating 3D shape surfaces using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of deep learning models for this task also suggests that it could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of residual networks, which are a type of neural network architecture commonly used in deep learning (cs.NE).
